                    <msContents>
                        <summary>The fourth volume of a five-volume set containing stories from the
                            Arabian Nights and other sources.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="manuscript_13837-item1">
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_700">Alf laylah
                                wa-laylah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar">الف ليلة وليلة</title>
                            <title xml:lang="en" type="supplied">A Thousand and One Nights</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                            <note><p>For the other volumes of the set, see <ref
                                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_13834"
                                        >Arabic MS 134</ref> (Vol. 1), <ref
                                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_13835"
                                        >Arabic MS 135</ref> (Vol. 2), <ref
                                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_13836"
                                        >Arabic MS 136</ref> (Vol. 3), <ref
                                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_13835"
                                        >Arabic MS 138</ref> (Vol. 5).</p>
                                <p>Each story is introduced as <quote>نبتدي بعون الله تعالي
                                        ونكتب</quote> (We begin with the help of Allah the Almighty
                                    and write...</p>.</note>
                            <incipit>نبتدي بعون الله تعالي ونكتب خبر</incipit>
                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_137-item1-item1">
                                <locus from="2b" to="16a">2b-16a</locus>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Khabar al-qahramānat wa-al-turjamānat
                                    wa-al-shābu ibn al-maliki wa-al-turjaman</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">خبر القهرمانة والترجمانة والشاب ابن
                                    الملك</title>
                                <title xml:lang="en">The butler, the interpreter and the young son
                                    of the king</title>
                                <note><p>Full title in manuscript: <quote xml:lang="ar">خبر
                                            القهرمانة والترجمانة والشاب ابن الملك وما جرى بينهما من
                                            المشاجرة وما صار بينهم </quote>.</p>
                                    <p>Mingana: the story of the son of the King of Rome who
                                        answered all the questions put to him by a daughter of
                                        another king.</p>
                                    <p>Cf. Manchester John Rylands Library, Arabic MS 557, folios
                                        44b-50a and Arabic MS 819, folios 96a-106.</p>
                                </note>
                                <incipit>نبتدي بعون الله تعالي وحسن</incipit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_137-item1-item2">
                                <locus from="17a" to="33a">17a-33a</locus>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Ḥikāyat mā ṣarat fī Baghdad bayn
                                    rajul ḥakīm wa-rajul tabakh</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">حكاية ما صارت في بغداد بين رجل حكيم ورجل
                                    طباخ</title>
                                <title xml:lang="en">The story of what happened in Baghdad between a
                                    wise man and a cook</title>
                                <note><p>Mingana: the story of a sorcerer and a cook. </p>
                                </note>
                                <incipit/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_137-item1-item3">
                                <locus from="34b" to="54a">34b-54a</locus>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Ḥikāyat al-māristān Dār
                                    al-Shifā</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">حكاية المارستان دار الشفا</title>
                                <title xml:lang="en">The story of the hospital</title>
                                <title xml:lang="en">The story of the bedlam Dar al-Shifā</title>
                                <note><p>Mingana: the story of the anecdotes told by the inmates of
                                        a lunatic asylum to the Caliph Hārūn al-Rashīd. </p>
                                </note>
                                <incipit/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_137-item1-item4">
                                <locus from="55b" to="75a">55b-75a</locus>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Qiṣat ʿAṭṭāf</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">قصة عطاف</title>
                                <title xml:lang="en">The story of ʿAṭṭāf</title>
                                <note><p>Mingana: the story of ʿAṭṭāf of Damascus who did much good
                                        to Jaʿfar, the vizier of Hārūn al-Rashīd. The story contains
                                        some Turkish words.</p>
                                </note>
                                <incipit/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_137-item1-item5">
                                <locus from="76b" to="106a">76b-106a</locus>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Ḥikāyat al-Sulṭān Ḥabīb</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">حكاية السلطان حبيب</title>
                                <title xml:lang="en">The story of Sultan Ḥabīb</title>
                                <note><p>Mingana: the story of Sultan Ḥabīb and Durrat al-Ghawwāṣ.
                                    </p>
                                </note>
                                <incipit/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_137-item1-item6">
                                <locus from="106b" to="124b">106b-124b</locus>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Ḥikāyat al-shāṭir Aḥmed
                                    al-Danf</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">حكاية الشاطر احمد الدنف</title>
                                <note><p>Full title in manuscript: <quote xml:lang="ar">كاية الشاطر
                                            احمد الدنف وما يقع له والجيليفه هارون الرشيد والصياد
                                            والقمقم النحاس</quote>, running title <quote
                                            xml:lang="ar">الخليفه والصياد</quote> (The Caliph and
                                        the fisherman).</p>
                                    <p>Mingana: the story of the fisherman, the Caliph, and the
                                        copper boiler.</p>
                                </note>
                                <incipit/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_137-item1-item7">
                                <locus from="126b" to="130b">126b-130b</locus>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Ḥikāyat laṭīfah jarat bayn al-diyk
                                    wa-al-taʿlab</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">حكاية لطيفه جرت بين الديك والتعلب</title>
                                <title xml:lang="en">The story of the cock and the fox.</title>
                                <note><p>The word fox is spelt as <quote xml:lang="ar">تعلب</quote>
                                        instead of <quote xml:lang="ar">ثعلب</quote>.</p>
                                </note>
                                <incipit/>
                            </msItem>

                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_137-item1-item78">
                                <locus from="131b" to="140b">131b-140b</locus>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Qiṣat al-ʿuṣfūr wa-mā jarā lahu maʿa
                                    al-sayyādi</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">قصت العصفور وما جري له مع الصياد</title>
                                <title xml:lang="en">The story of the sparrow and the
                                    hunter.</title>
                                <note><p>Running title <quote xml:lang="ar">العصفور والصياد</quote>
                                        (The sparrow and the hunter).</p>
                                </note>
                                <incipit>بسم اله والبن والروح القدس</incipit>
                            </msItem>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
